                <article class="post-36805 page type-page status-publish hentry">

                    <section class="kanji">
	                	<h1>静</h1>
<h4>Quiet</h4>
<p><strong>On&#8217;yomi: </strong>せい<br />
<strong>Kun&#8217;yomi: </strong>しず.か<br />
<strong>Radicals:</strong> Blue + Conflict</p>
<h2>Meaning: Quiet</h2>
<p><span class="aradical">Conflict</span> in <span class="aradical">blue</span> water is made <span class="akanji">quiet</span> by the muffling power of water. Under this blue water is a great conflict between two sea monsters, but on the surface it appears peaceful and quiet as the water prevents sound from rising above the surface.</p>
<p>Imagine watching this conflict from above the blue water on a boat. You can see all of the action but its eerily quiet as you cannot hear any of the noise.</p>
<h2>Reading: せい</h2>
<p>It’s <span class="akanji">quiet</span>. To break the silence, Hard Gay jumps onto the poop deck and shouts, “<span class="areading">Sei</span> (せい), sei, sei~!” and starts hip thrusting violently. Now you don’t know whether to watch him, or concentrate on the conflict under the blue waters.</p>
<p>Picture yourself trying to concentrate on the quiet battle under the sea as Hard Gay parades around the ship, gyrating and shouting, “Sei, sei, sei~!” It’s quite distracting.</p>
<h2>Related Vocabulary</h2>
<h3>静か    しずか    Quiet</h3>
<h3>冷静    れいせい    Cool Headed, Calm</h3>
<ul>
<li>冷 (Cool) + 静 (Quiet)</li>
</ul>
<h3>静々    しずしず    Quietly, Calmly</h3>
<ul>
<li>静 (Quiet) + 々 (Repeater)</li>
</ul>
<h3>静止    せいし    Still, Standstill, At Rest, Stationary</h3>
<ul>
<li>静 (Quiet) + 止 (Stop)</li>
</ul>
<h3>平静    へいせい    Calm, Serene, Tranquil</h3>
<ul>
<li>平 (Flat) + 静 (Quiet)</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="btn large" href="勉.1.html#top">← 勉</a> <a class="btn large" href="温.1.html#top">温 →</a></p>
